editorialNotes.standard: The moment we met wee kitty Crumbs in Little Kitten, we let out an audible “awww.” This adorable digital feline encourages children to play and explore, interacting with the lively toys and simple games in Crumbs’ room. We’re amazed by the cinematic animation, and appreciate the sleep timer that sends Crumbs to bed when our kids’ screen time is over.

editorialNotes.standard: This charming bedtime story will soothe your young child with delightful imagery and a simple but engaging spoken tale. Intuitive controls and fun interactive surprises make Nighty Night a pleasure to explore, and with optional narration, you and your toddler can settle in to be entertained or bring your own imaginations to the wonderful nighttime world.
